{{Infobox language |name=Bosha |nativename=Garo |states=[[Ethiopia]] |region=[[Kingdom of Garo]] |extinct=fl. through 19th century |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Omotic languages|Omotic]] |fam3=(see text) |iso3=none |iso3comment=(included in {{ethnolink|kbr}}) |glotto=bosh1241 |glottorefname=Bosha }}
'''Bosha''' is an extinct [[Omotic language]] of [[Ethiopia]]. ''[[Ethnologue]]'' lists it as a dialect of the Northern Omotic [[Kafa language]], but notes that it may be a distinct language. Other sources list it as unclassified.<ref>Blench, 2006. [http://rogerblench.info/Language/Afroasiatic/General/AALIST.pdf The Afro-Asiatic Languages: Classification and Reference List]</ref> The Bosha state, the [[Kingdom of Garo]], was a culturally [[Gonga languages|Gonga]] enclave within the southern [[Oromo language|Oromo]] area.
