'''Flight hours''' is a term meaning the hours or time spent in the [[sky]] on an [[aircraft]]. Usually, it is meant to show the experience of pilots, with the more flight hours a [[Aircraft pilot|pilot]] has, the more experience. It can also refer to passengers' flight time as to frequency of flight.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.law.cornell.edu/cfr/text/14/121.481 | title = Flight time limitations: One or two pilot crews | date = 26 January 1996 | accessdate = 12 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.lawinsider.com/dictionary/flight-hours | title = Flight Hours- legal definition of Flight Hours by Lawinsider.com | accessdate = 12 January 2018}}</ref>

