'''Gohar Markosjan-Käsper''' ({{lang-hy|Գոհար Մարկոսյան-Կասպեր}}; 14 July 1949, [[Yerevan]] &ndash; 15 September 2015, [[Barcelona]]) was an [[Armenians|Armenian]] writer who lived in [[Tallinn]], [[Estonia]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Gohar Marcossian |publisher=Bibliomonde.net |url=http://www.bibliomonde.net/pages/fiche-auteur.php3?id_auteur=2065 |accessdate=2010-01-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Penelope, die Listenreiche |work=Büchermarkt |publisher=Deutschlandfunk/Dradio.de |date=2010-01-20 |url=http://www.dradio.de/dlf/sendungen/buechermarkt/165476/ |accessdate=2010-01-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=ELU ÜHES PÄEVAS: Gohar Markosjan-Käsper |language=Estonian |work=Eesti Ekspress |publisher=Ekspress.ee |url=http://www.ekspress.ee/viewdoc/C8F1B66C2D6F2D10C225701300316B0C |first=Birgit |last=Püve |date=2005-06-02 |accessdate=2010-01-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Прозрачные слова Гоар Маркосян-Кяспер |work=Postimees |publisher=rus.postimees.ee |date=2006-08-03 |url=http://rus.postimees.ee/030806/glavnaja/kultura/3198.php |author=Игорь Котюх |accessdate=2010-01-24}}</ref>
==Life== Her father was an opera singer and mother a ballet-dancer. She graduated the [[Yerevan State Medical school]] as a doctor. She married [[Kalle Käsper]], an Estonian writer and translator, in 1990. Before moving to Estonia, Gohar Markosjan used to work as a doctor in [[Yerevan]].
==Work as a writer== Markosjan-Käsper's best-known work is probably the novel ''Penelope'' (translated into French, German - as ''Penelope, die Listenreiche'',<ref>''[http://www.egotrip.de/bucher/03/0310_penelope.html Gohar Morkosjan-Kasper: "Penelope, die Listenreiche". Eine literarische Verneigung vor Joyce und Homer]'' {{de icon}}</ref> Dutch and Spanish) <!-- also?-->. Her novels ''Helena'' and ''The Caryatides''<ref>{{cite web |author=Я.Йняршпйн, Р.Рхунмнбю |url=http://magazines.russ.ru/zvezda/2003/8/goar-pr.html |title=Text in Russian |publisher=magazines.russ.ru | date=August 2003 |accessdate=2010-01-24}}</ref> have also been successful in Russia and Western Europe. Her works have been characterized as [[magical realist]].
She wrote in [[Russian language|Russian]]. Markosjan-Käsper was also a member of the [[Estonian Writers' Union]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ekl.ee/liikmed.html |title=Eesti Kirjanike Liit |publisher={{url|ekl.ee}} |date= |accessdate=2010-01-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100301100926/http://www.ekl.ee/liikmed.html |archivedate=2010-03-01 |df= }}</ref>
